ing paper so that it hangs over the edge."},{"content":"On a clean work surface, place one sheet of filo and quickly brush with melted butter then place another sheet on top and brush again with butter. Place one nut paste roll on the long side and roll up to form a long log. Repeat with remaining paste and filo sheets to form 4 logs."},{"content":"Shape the first log into a tight coil. Place coil in centre of springform base, brush the loose end generously with melted butter and attach end of next log. Coil second log around outside of first. Continue with remaining logs until base of tin is covered."},{"content":"Attach the outside of the springform tin to the base with the coil neatly inside."},{"content":"In a small bowl, mix egg yolk and cinnamon then brush over filo coil with pastry brush. Sprinkle with flaked almonds and bake for 30-35 minutes (170°C) until pastry is golden brown. Towards the end of this time, make syrup."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Syrup"},{"content":"Place orange juice and honey in mixing bowl then cook <b>10 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Remove coil from oven and allow to sit for 5 minutes, then spoon over syrup, leaving to stand a further 20 minutes before removing from tin and serving."}],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 15m","12 portions"]}